history.text: Hi!  Have you seen Mean Girls?
Hi, I guess I did sometime but I don't remember it
It's a good one?
Oh it's great,  it's about Cady Heron, she's a new student at a highschool,  shes only ever been homeschooled. She discovers social cliques and shows how they damage girls.
Lindsay Lohan plays Cady
Oh, I like Lindsay Lohan, she has made good funny movies
Yeah she has.  This movie got rated The Top 50 Greatest Teen Comedies.
By Rotten Tomatoes
Wow, I did'nt knew that. I guess I should give it a chance then, thanks.
Do you like Tina Fey?
I'm not very familiar with her
Who is she?
Oh she's an actress, comedian and writer.  She wrote this movie alongside Mark Waters.
Awesome, I didn't know that. Freaky Friday, which Mark Waters wrote too, is one of my favorites movies.
I love Freaky Friday too,  I didnt know he wrote that one too.
He directed* it, my bad.
Oh well cool.
Definitively I will look at Mean Girls now that I know those facts.
Yeah its a good movie.  Have you seen Ted 2?
Eh.. I guess not, I only have seen Ted 1

Oh well. Uh Amanda Seyfried is in bot
h movies.
What kind of movies do you like?
Oh. I really like thriller and sci-fi movies, I like comedy/romance too.
What about you?
Thrillers,  comedies,  action. Some sci-fi
Nice.
Anything you wanna know about Mean Girls?
Hmm I don't know, more about the plot?

Cady goes to a new school,  meets Janice and Damien, her new friends warn her to stay away from the Plastics,  which Regina George is the leader. They're popular, beautiful and crude. Regina is dating Aaron Samuels. Can't basically falls in love with Aaron and Regina finds out she gets mad and tortures Cady. Then Cast begins to like Regina and becomes one of the Plastics.
Auto correct changed Cady to Cast.
I see.. a bit strange/funny "then cady begins to like Regina" haha thanks

uid2response.feedback: After knowing it was directed by the same who directed Freaky Friday sure I will watch it.
